<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUL 93 / London Stock Exchange: Equity futures and options trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TECHNICAL action shook stock index futures which have recently been treading
water and brisk selling was followed by a rally that left the September
contract at a healthy premium to the cash market, Christine Buckley writes.
The expiry yesterday morning of the July contract on index options
stimulated dealers to gauge their positions in futures. The contract opened
at 2,840 and quickly fell to 2,827 as selling started. It stayed around that
level until 10.30am signalled the end of the July contract and then futures
set off upwards. Some bounce came from the lower-than-expected public sector
borrowing requirement figures.
The contract closed at 2,847 putting it just over 8 points ahead of its fair
value premium to cash of 7 points. Volume was 7,512 lots. Traded options
kept a steady volume at 26,418 lots with the July contract expiry triggering
action in index options - the FT-SE 100 option was 8,254 and the Euro FT-SE
100 option at 4,991.
</TEXT>
