<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUL 93 / Prospect of renewed fighting overshadows start of summit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTHONY ROBINSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUDAPEST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE prospect of renewed fighting between Serbs and Croats for the recovery
of Croatian territory overshadowed the start of a two-day summit meeting
between central European leaders yesterday which is aimed at easing ethnic
conflicts and increasing regional co-operation, Anthony Robinson writes from
Budapest.
Serbia has been excluded from the Central European Initiative (CEI) summit,
which provides a forum for meetings between the prime ministers and foreign
ministers of Italy and eight central European countries. Today Macedonia is
due to join the CEI, which was launched in 1989 as a five-nation group
cutting across the divide between Nato and Warsaw Pact countries.
