<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUL 93 / MI5 chief moves out of shadows into spotlight
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MRS STELLA Rimington, director-general of Britain's internal Security
Service, posed under conditions of appropriate secrecy for her first
official photographs yesterday.
Press photographers, summoned to the Home Office for an undisclosed
assignment, were taken by minibus to the service's headquarters. The
curtains of Mrs Rimington's office were drawn to avoid identifying the
room's location within the building.
The photograph is a step forward for open government: Mrs Rimington is the
first director-general of the Security Service - still widely known by its
1916 title MI5 - to have been officially identified while in office. The
government also published yesterday a booklet on MI5 on staffing and fields
of operation.
