FT  16 JUL 93 / International Company News: Spain extends credit facility
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SARA WEBB
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Kingdom of Spain is to increase its recently-announced borrowing
facility to Ecu5bn from Ecu4bn, reflecting the willingness of banks to
participate in the deal, Sara Webb writes.
The three-year, multi-currency revolving credit facility is the largest
financing to be put together by a European government this year. It was
arranged by NatWest Capital Markets.
