<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 93 / Parliament and Politics: Caterer settles libel action
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DOWNING STREET caterer Ms Clare Latimer settled her libel action against
Scallywag magazine yesterday, leaving the prime minister to continue his
legal battle alone.
Scallywag immediately threw down the gauntlet and challenged Mr John Major
to a full-scale libel trial.
Mr David Price, the magazine's solicitor, said: 'The first law of libel is
that you should not start something you cannot finish. We will see if Mr
Major is prepared to meet my clients in court.'
Miss Latimer said the defendants could not bring themselves to apologise and
they had no means to meet any claims for damages or costs.
She added: 'In the circumstances, as they agreed to undertake to the court
not to repeat the allegations, I am content to have reached a settlement.'
Mr David Hooper, Mr Major's solicitor, confirmed that the prime minister's
action against the magazine was unaffected by the settlement with Miss
Latimer and was continuing.
</TEXT>
